Please notice that the *online version did not display the vertical scale correctly*. It displayed all the columns and the ages correctly.

 

In addition: I selected the British and the Belgian datapacks (time interval 290 – 350 Ma and vertical scale 1) and enlarged the width of the “NW Belgium (Maastricht) --> Campine Basin-Maasmelchen” to 100 from 40.

I saved a settings file: *Britain_Belgium.tsc.* If I reload the settings into the online TSC, the width for the column reverted to 40 and the vertical scale is 2 instead of 1. It seems that the vertical scale is somewhere hardwired into your system. If I load this settings file into the desktop TSC, then the vertical scale is displayed correctly at 1, but the column width is 40.

 

I also generated the same settings file in the desktop version (*Desktop_Britai_Belgium.tsc*). If I load it into the Online version, it displays correctly with column width of 100 and vertical scale 1.
